Genevieve Quintal, News24Crystal meth (File, SAPS) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Crystal meth with a street value of R7.5m was intercepted by custom officials at OR International Airport on Friday night, the SA Revenue Service said.The drugs were found during an inspection of a flight from Cotonou, Benin in West Africa, Sars spokesperson Sandile Memela said."All unaccompanied bags were escorted to the Sars customs search area for scanning where 25 plastic bags containing a white substance were found in one of the bags."The substance tested positive for crystal methamphetamine - better known as tik in South Africa.The bags weighed a total of 25.20kgs and had a street value of R7 560 000, he said. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.